org.microbean.kubernetes.controller

Class Event<T extends HasMetadata>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • org.microbean.kubernetes.controller.Event<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - a type of Kubernetes resource
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Event<T extends HasMetadata>
extends EventObject
    An EventObject that represents another event that has occurred to a Kubernetes resource, usually as found in an EventCache implementation.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    EventCache, Serialized Form

      • getPriorResource

        public final T getPriorResource()
        Returns a HasMetadata representing the prior state of the Kubernetes resource this Event primarily concerns.

        This method may return null, and often does.

        The prior state of a Kubernetes resource is often not known at Event construction time so it is common for this method to return null.

        Returns:
        a HasMetadata representing the prior state of the Kubernetes resource this Event primarily concerns, or null
        See Also:
        getResource()
